+section("Country Flags")
  p Country flags are circular SVG images with a transparent background. To use the flags in your project, simply add the following code to your HTML: <code>&lt;img src="/assets/img/flags/{country-code}.svg" alt="{country-name}" /&gt;</code>. For example, to use the flag of Australia, add the following code to your HTML: <code>&lt;img src="img/flags/au.svg" alt="Australia" /&gt;</code>. See the list of country codes below or <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ISO_3166_country_codes" target="_blank">click here</a> to view the list of country codes on Wikipedia.

+section("Flag Sizes", "h5")
  p We have special scale classes for flags. These classes are used to scale the flags to the appropriate size. The scale sizes increases by a factor of "4" from 4 till 256. To scale a flag, simply add the class <code>.flag-w{size}</code> to the icon element. For example, to scale an icon to 64px, add the class <code>.flag-w64</code> to the img tag. See <code>/src/sass/components/_flags.scss</code> for the full list of scale classes.

  p Scale sizes are also available for multiple breakpoints (small, medium, large). To use the scale size classes for a specific breakpoint, simply add the breakpoint name to the class. For example, to scale a flag to 64px on medium screens, add the class <code>.medium-flag-w64</code> to the icon element.

